  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Associate - Legal",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>We are seeking a lawyer to join its in-house legal team in Singapore. The organisation operates across SEA (principally in Singapore) and China. The role offers broad exposure to general commercial and corporate matters, supporting business, mid-offices, back office and transactions across multiple jurisdictions.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Advise, draft, support a wide range of general commercial contracts including NDAs, introducer agreements, vendor and supplier contracts, services agreements, collaborative agreements, and operational contracts</li></ul><ul><li>Draft and manage corporate secretarial documents such as Directors’ Resolutions In Writing and board minutes to ensure compliance and governance standards</li></ul><ul><li>Provide legal input and support to investment and non-investment teams on commercial and investment-related documents to facilitate transaction execution</li></ul><ul><li>Deliver day-to-day legal advice and support to investment teams, non-investment teams, and internal stakeholders to mitigate legal risks and enable business decisions</li></ul><ul><li>Execute ad-hoc legal assignments for group companies as directed by the direct supervisor</li></ul><ul><li>Assist direct supervisor with fund management legal activities, including reviewing fund offering documents such as Private Placement Memoranda, Offering Memorandum, Management Agreements, fund subscription agreements, and brokerage-related agreements</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Law and qualification to practice in Singapore or at least one common law jurisdiction</li></ul><ul><li>Proficiency in Mandarin (spoken and written) to support regional and China-related legal matters</li></ul><ul><li>2 years PQE</li></ul><ul><li>Legal experience gained in fund management is a Plus</li></ul><ul><li>Strong experience in drafting and negotiating commercial contracts</li></ul><ul><li>Ability to work independently with self-initiative, manage multiple concurrent tasks, and adapt to a fast-growing environment</li></ul><ul><li>Strong organizational skills with meticulousness and resourcefulness</li></ul><ul><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint</li></ul>",
